This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring June 14 as Flag Day and the week beginning June 12 as National Flag Week. The proclamation highlights the significance of the American flag as a symbol of the country's unity and ideals. It mentions how the flag has been present throughout the nation's history, representing liberty and democracy both at home and abroad. The proclamation also calls upon Americans to display the flag during this week and encourages public gatherings and activities to honor America's heritage. It concludes with President Obama's signature and the date of the proclamation.